    "reasoning": "To implement the timer module, we need to create a down-counter that decrements the count every clock cycle. When the load input is high, the counter should be loaded with the new value from the data input. When the load is low, the counter should decrement. The terminal count (tc) output should be high when the counter reaches zero. We use a single D flip-flop to store the current count. The reset input is active high synchronous and resets the counter to zero.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input wire clk,\n    input wire load,\n    input wire [9:0] data,\n    output wire tc\n);\n\n    // Counter register\n    logic [9:0] counter;\n\n    // Terminal count flag\n    logic tc_flag;\n\n    // Always block for updating the counter\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (reset)\n            counter <= 10'b0;\n        else if (load)\n            counter <= data;\n        else if (counter != 0)\n            counter <= counter - 1;\n    end\n\n    // Always block for calculating the terminal count flag\n    always @(*) begin\n        tc_flag = (counter == 0);\n    end\n\n    // Assign the terminal count flag to the output\n    assign tc = tc_flag;\n\nendmodule"
